This paper discusses website authentication using Tor's onion system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the advantages of using onion sites for authentication, which could be relevant to the categories of computer networks (cs.CY), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed computing (cs.DC), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
